lines.text: PROFESSIONAL INSECT CONTROL ROACH KILLER SMALL BAIT STATIONS
MAXFORCE PROFESSIONAL INSECT CONTROL ROACH KILLER SMALL BAIT STATIONS
ODORLESS, PALE YELLOW TO YELLOWISH-BROWN WAXY MASS WITH SUSPENDED PARTICULATE MATTER.
Toxicity Data, Effects of Overexposure, Emergency & First Aid Procedures
The acute oral LD50 in both male and female rats is > 5000mg/kg
indicating this product to be practically non-toxic by oral route of exposure.
The acute dermal LD50 in both male and female rabbits is > 2000mg/kg,
indicating this product to be no more than slightly toxic by dermal route of
This product is not irritating to rabbit skin.
Ingredients Listed By NTP. OSHA or TARC as carcinogens or potential
This product may produce slight irritation upon ocular contact
Untoward effects resulting from overexposure are not anticipated to occur
because this formulation is packaged in a child-resistant container.
Health conditions aggravated by exposure: none known
Flash Points: >200 F CC (Method: Closed Cup)
Appearance and Odor: Odorless, Pale Yellow to Yellowish-Brown Waxy
Fire Extinguishing Media: Water, Foam, Carbon Dioxide or Dry Chemical.
Unusual Fire And Explosion Hazards: None
Steps to be taken in case material is released or spilled: place in a
Waste disposal: dispose in accord with local, state, and federal regulations.
Hazardous Decomposition Products: Thermal Decomposition May Produce
Carbon Monoxide, Carbon Dioxide, Methane, and Oxides of Nitrogen and
None required under normal conditions of use.
